Yobe State governor, Mai Mala Buni, has been appointed as Chairman of the All Progressives Congress Caretaker Committee and extraordinary National Convention. This was announced on Thursday during a meeting where President Muhammadu Buhari dissolved the National Working Committee of the party. According to a presidential aide, Bashir Ahmad, on Twitter, Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, governors, National Assembly leaders and top members of the party all attended the meeting. See Also






